HEADWORD: Zamia
<hw>Za"mi*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>zamia</ets> a kind of fir cone, from Gr. <?/, <?/, hurt, damage.
See Plin. xvi. 44.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of cycadaceous
plants, having the appearance of low palms, but with exogenous wood. See
